description:
&lt;p&gt;Salaried GP – 4-8 sessions&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;St Lukes Surgery, Abercarn, Gwent&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;St Lukes is a practice of 4 partners and 1 salaried GP looking to expand our team by recruiting another enthusiastic GP. With a registered list of just over 7,600 the practice is situated in Abercarn - an easy commute from Cardiff, Newport and the Brecon Beacons.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt; An innovative practice actively taking measures to reduce GP workload whilst providing excellent patient care&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; Our team includes:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;2 GP Appraisers&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Medico-legal expert&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prescribing pharmacists to support medicines management and audit&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Community Nurse Practitioner undertaking home visits&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent practice nursing team leading chronic disease management&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;NCN Cluster Physiotherapist and Pharmacist&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Highly skilled practice management&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Team of Prescription clerks&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experienced and friendly administration and reception team providing full support to clinicians&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Frontline staff fully trained in signposting&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Additional information:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Medical student teaching with links to the Cardiff University School of Medicine&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;All existing partners and salaried GPs work on a part-time basis, so we would consider a job share arrangement to help achieve the best work/life balance&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Flexible working including start times, and number of sessions is open to negotiation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Possibility of fixed days&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Personal postgraduate development is actively encouraged and supported&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Attractive and competitive remuneration&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are offering the opportunity to experience a wide range of general practice in a friendly and relaxed environment with the time to explore and expand your personal interests and to fulfil your career aims&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Informal enquiries and visits are welcomed.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;For further information please contact Mrs Jenny Powell (Practice Manager) on 01495 244205; or e-mail Dr Julian Sweetman - Julian.sweetman@wales.nhs.uk&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
